# Home Assistant Configuration
# Standalone instance with host networking for full device discovery

# ===================================
# General Settings
# ===================================

# Server timezone
TZ=America/Vancouver

# Home Assistant image tag (default: stable)
IMAGE_TAG=stable

# ===================================
# DNS / Access
# ===================================

# Local DNS hostname (add to Pi-hole: homeassistant.italicninja.com -> 192.168.1.10)
DNS_HOSTNAME=homeassistant.italicninja.com

# ===================================
# Storage Paths
# ===================================

# Host path for persistent configuration data
# Must exist before starting: mkdir -p /data/homeassistant/config
HA_CONFIG_PATH=/data/homeassistant/config

# ===================================
# Usage Notes
# ===================================

# 1. Create data directory before starting:
#    mkdir -p /data/homeassistant/config
#
# 2. Deploy via Portainer:
#    - Create stack from Git repository
#    - Compose path: compose/homeassistant.yml
#    - Load these environment variables in Portainer UI
#
# 3. Access Home Assistant:
#    - Local: http://192.168.1.10:8123
#    - DNS:   http://homeassistant.italicninja.com:8123
#
# 4. First-run setup:
#    - Navigate to http://192.168.1.10:8123 after startup
#    - Complete the onboarding wizard (create account, set location, etc.)
#    - Takes ~60-120 seconds to be ready on first boot
#
# 5. Pi-hole DNS entry (required for local name resolution):
#    - Access Pi-hole: https://pihole.italicninja.com:8443/admin
#    - Local DNS -> DNS Records
#    - Domain: homeassistant.italicninja.com
#    - IP:     192.168.1.10
#
# 6. Network mode is set to "host" to allow:
#    - mDNS / Zeroconf device discovery
#    - SSDP / UPnP discovery (e.g. Google Cast, Sonos)
#    - Bluetooth proxy (if using a USB adapter)
#    - Direct LAN communication without NAT
#
# 7. Port Forwarding (optional remote access):
#    - External 8123 -> 192.168.1.10:8123 (TCP)
#    - Or expose via nginx reverse proxy with HTTPS
#
# 8. Resource Requirements:
#    - Minimum: 512MB RAM
#    - Recommended: 1-2GB RAM for automations and integrations
#    - CPU: 1-2 cores recommended
